The paper deals with stochastic optimal control problems with risk constraints, which are typically studied in the control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO) communities. The use of martingales and sampling-based algorithms suggests a focus on algorithmic and computational aspects, which are relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. Finally, the use of probability theory and information theory concepts suggests a possible connection to the information theory (cs.IT) community.
